Map
===
a Map is an interface that stores data as: Key → Value

Key Rules:
----------
    Keys are unique
    Values can be duplicated
    Each key maps to exactly one value

Common Implementations:
-----------------------
    HashMap: Unordered, allows null keys/values, not thread-safe
    TreeMap: Sorted by keys, no null keys, not thread-safe
    LinkedHashMap: Maintains insertion order, allows null keys/values, not thread-safe


Why Map is Used?
----------------
    Fast lookup
    Key-based storage
    Counting / tracking

-------------------------
map.getOrDefault(key, 0)  ->  returns value for key or 0 if key not present
-------------------------

map.getOrDefault(key, 0) is used in:
------------------------------------
    Counting elements
    Finding duplicates
    Anagrams
    Subarray Sum = K ⭐
    Most frequent element


